      • getClientBlockUnmappedActions

        public boolean getClientBlockUnmappedActions()
        Returns:
        a boolean flag indicating whether actions, submitted as tasks in an Executor from clients and have no permission mappings, are blocked or allowed.

        Executors:

        • IExecutorService
        • IScheduledExecutorService
        • DurableExecutorService

      • setClientBlockUnmappedActions

        public SecurityConfig setClientBlockUnmappedActions(boolean clientBlockUnmappedActions)
        Block or allow actions, submitted as tasks in an Executor from clients and have no permission mappings.

        Executors:

        • IExecutorService
        • IScheduledExecutorService
        • DurableExecutorService
        Parameters:
        clientBlockUnmappedActions -
      • True: Blocks all actions that have no permission mapping
      • False: Allows all actions that have no permission mapping
